[0.242961, "o", "\r\nThe pre-fix code in main (commit 00a1f3c60) had NO trustedWorkspaces\r\npre-seed block in packages/plugins/agent-antigravity/src/index.ts.\r\nOn that code, the new tests in\r\npackages/plugins/agent-antigravity/src/index.trustedWorkspaces.test.ts\r\nwould all FAIL because the production code never writes to the inner\r\nantigravity-cli/settings.json file.\r\n\r\n"]
[0.244166, "o", "Red phase captured from running the test file against\r\npackages/plugins/agent-antigravity/src/index.ts as of 00a1f3c60:\r\n\r\n"]
[0.249336, "o", "Test Files  1 failed (1)\r\n     Tests  3 failed | 1 passed (4)\r\n  × pre-seeds antigravity-cli/settings.json trustedWorkspaces\r\n    → expected false to be true // Object.is equality\r\n    ❯ src/index.trustedWorkspaces.test.ts:154:49\r\n      expect(writtenFiles.has(innerSettingsPath)).toBe(true);\r\n                                                ^\r\n  × merges with existing trustedWorkspaces\r\n    → the given combination of arguments (undefined and string) is invalid\r\n    ❯ src/index.trustedWorkspaces.test.ts:212:45\r\n      expect(innerSettings.trustedWorkspaces).toContain(\"/already/trusted/path\");\r\n                                              ^\r\n  × does not overwrite antigravity-cli/settings.json when parse fails\r\n    → expected false to be true // Object.is equality\r\n    ❯ src/index.trustedWorkspaces.test.ts:287:7\r\n      ).toBe(true);\r\n       ^\r\n  ✓ does not throw when antigravity-cli/settings.json is missing\r\n"]
